<br>
No need to get shitty w/ me, that's just the way this spawn has been handled since it was moved to Skyfire. Its a first come first serve spawn and you can thank Verant for that. Of course, here on RZ, there's other ways to decide who gets dibs. <p><b>Kilyin, <a href="http://www.ascendingdawn.com">Ascending Dawn</a><br>
High Priest of Innoruuk<br>
<a href="http://www.ascendingdawn.com/cgi-bin/ad.pl?page=inspect&id=104">Character Profile</a></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uavih8r.showPublicProfile?language=EN>avih8r</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#333333>(4/24/02 1:43:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=797.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whaaagh And RageFire And AD</span><hr size=1> &gt; I wasn't aware Ragefire was a suite at the Marriot Inn. How do you plan to 'book' him?<br>
&gt; Whoever has the force to kill him first, will. Simple as that.<br>
<br>
This gets funnier by the minute.  The entire reason Syn/AD teamed up to war Rebirth was because we wouldn't join your stupid spawn rotation.  Now you've changed your tune?  Lol.<br>
<br>
You guys are fucking hypocrits, and I think it's hilarious.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ukilyinrz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KilyinRZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#333333>(4/24/02 1:54:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=797.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/kilyin/hartman.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whaaagh And RageFire And AD</span><hr size=1> Josheb you're a fucking moron.  Nobody said we refuse rotations, but it's kind of hard to schedule a RANDOM SPAWN that can be anywhere from 3 to 7 days.  Here's some clues for you, skippy. <br>
<br>
Clue 1: Verant changed the Ragefire spawn, and moved it to Skyfire. It's now completely random and can't be triggered.<br>
<br>
Clue 2: I'm speaking in general, as we don't even need anymore Ragefires to my knowledge. Since the spawn was changed though, it has pretty much been FCFS. <br>
<br>
Clue 3: Rebirth was ran off the server because they were assholes who refused *any* and *all* attempts at coming to a compromise on spawns.<br>
<br>
Clue 4: You 'quit' EQ, or so you claim... so why don't you shut the fuck up since you obviously have *no idea* what goes on in a game you don't play anymore.<br>
<br>
 <p><b>Kilyin, <a href="http://www.ascendingdawn.com">Ascending Dawn</a><br>
High Priest of Innoruuk<br>
<a href="http://www.ascendingdawn.com/cgi-bin/ad.pl?page=inspect&id=104">Character Profile</a></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uavih8r.showPublicProfile?language=EN>avih8r</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#333333>(4/24/02 2:06:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=797.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whaaagh And RageFire And AD</span><hr size=1> It's an issue of respect..  If someone is there camping Ragefire, you just said you're willing to disrespect them and take the spawn.<br>
<br>
It doesn't take a brain surgeon to figure out that AD is in the best position to get a force there to kill RF first.  You have the largest number of decently geared people on the server, and you could take RF down with considerably less people than any other guild.<br>
<br>
You can call me names all you like, it's just your reflex reaction to not liking what I have to say.  AD makes up rules on the fly as they suit the current situation -- you can't argue that.  If the tables were turned around, your position wouldn't be the same.. you would be whining that your twink was there for 2 days camping the spawn and someone else stole it from you.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ukellaer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kellaer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 358<br> <font color=#333333>(4/24/02 2:11:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=797.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whaaagh And RageFire And AD</span><hr size=1> There's differences between: <br>
<br>
1.  A mob with fixed spawn times that pops on server repop and follows a set schedule until server down time (see - damn near everything during the rebirth war)<br>
<br>
2.  A mob that spawns randomly after another mob is killed, hence requiring some effort to spawn it in the first place (see old ragefire)<br>
<br>
3.  A mob that just pops randomly in skyfire, requiring no effort from anyone, except the effort of camping it to see if it's up (see new ragefire)<br>
<br>
I'm sure someone will correct me if I'm wrong, but it's been a LONG time since an AD cleric went epic.  We aren't hoarding these spawns.  <br>
<br>
It's too bad people we usually have no trouble working with felt the need to involve GMs in the matter.  It's also too bad that the cleric epic seems to have been designed with the intention of causing problems between players who compete over it.<br>
<br>
Josheb, why don't you go troll stormhammer message boards with your weak ass friends who couldn't handle rallos anymore, so they ran off to legends?  I suppose I should give you more credit than them... at least you had the sense to quit the game, instead of skulking away like a dog with your tail between your legs to a new server.<br>
<br>
kellaer<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ukilyinrz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KilyinRZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#333333>(4/24/02 2:13:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=797.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/kilyin/hartman.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whaaagh And RageFire And AD</span><hr size=1> You might have a relevant point if Sallox hadn't been camping it all week. He simply got lucky that AD was able to mobilize quickly enough when Rage did indeed spawn. Otherwise, the fact he had been camping it would have meant jack and shit to the other guilds/groups who came there to kill Ragefire. <br>
<br>
Let me spell that out for you. People were not going to respect Sallox's camp. He even has screenshots showing him as being in the zone by himself. The only reason he got his epic is because everyone online at the time rushed to Skyfire to kill Rage. Get it?<br>
<br>
Nobody on any server is respecting a 'camp' on Ragefire. It's the nature of the beast. <p><b>Kilyin, <a href="http://www.ascendingdawn.com">Ascending Dawn</a><br>
High Priest of Innoruuk<br>
<a href="http://www.ascendingdawn.com/cgi-bin/ad.pl?page=inspect&id=104">Character Profile</a></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/upikawel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>pikawel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#333333>(4/25/02 3:13:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=797.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pikawel.com/retard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whaaagh And RageFire And AD</span><hr size=1> Wow, that is officially the worst signature ever.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://rohan.sdsu.edu/~gphie/jalal.jpg">rohan.sdsu.edu/~gphie/jalal.jpg</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p><center><img src="http://pikawel.com/movesig2.jpg"><br>You obviously lack the creative genius to integrate Legos and Duplos.</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=doslingos>DosLingos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(4/28/02 8:07:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=797.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What?</span><hr size=1> &quot;In this particular instant my statement does imply that. However, every spawn is different and our rulesets differ depending on what we're talking about. &quot;<br>
<br>
So you're saying that if a guild has one member in the zone and is &quot;camping&quot; ragefire and it spawns, then they have the right to kill it even if it takes them an hour to get there?  Pretty stupid ruleset. <br>
<br>
Newbie01 says out of character 'Sorry guys, I know we only have 3 peeps in the zone, but I was camping ragefire. Please leave it alone until my guild can get together and get here.'<br>
<br>
If you're &quot;camping&quot; the spawn, then you need to have 15 people with you ready to take it out when it pops, or better be prepared to tank until your guild gets there. Whoever engages first makes sense to me.  This isn't the orc trainer dude, you don't &quot;camp&quot; a mob like that.<br>
<br>
If you guys can get your asses in gear and get to the spawn, be ready, and engage, it should be yours until you fail.  If it takes you 30 mins to be prepared and another guild can get there and kick it's ass first, then that's your own fault. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=doslingos>DosLingos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(4/28/02 8:10:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=797.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> s</span><hr size=1> &quot;It's an issue of respect.. If someone is there camping Ragefire, you just said you're willing to disrespect them and take the spawn.&quot;<br>
<br>
You don't &quot;camp&quot; the spawn.  You sit a mule or your char in the zone so that you're one of the first to know when it's up, and can alert your guild before anyone gets there. If you're &quot;camping&quot; a spawn, it shouldn't take you 20 mins to engage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=doslingos>DosLingos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(4/28/02 8:12:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=797.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> d</span><hr size=1> &quot;You might have a relevant point if Sallox hadn't been camping it all week... Nobody on any server is respecting a 'camp' on Ragefire. It's the nature of the beast. &quot;<br>
<br>
That's because the idea of someone being able to sit in a zone for a week and claiming a camp of a random, non-triggered mob is ludicrous.  Only way I could see as him &quot;owning&quot; the camp is if he had been there all week killing PH and forcing it to spawn. Sitting on your ass in a zone when something pops doesn't mean it's yours.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wizpk>WizPK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(4/28/02 8:14:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=797.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> -</span><hr size=1> AD doesnt hafta talk to you, cuz they have better gear.  <br>
